---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy Policy for paulxie.com" />
		<style>
			.prose {
				max-width: min(1080px, calc(100% - 2em));
				margin: auto;
				padding: 1em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
			}
			.prose h1 {
				text-align: center;
				margin-bottom: 0.5em;
			}
			.prose h2 {
				border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
				padding-bottom: 0.3em;
			}
			.summary {
				background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.3);
				border-left: 3px solid rgb(var(--accent, var(--gray)));
				padding: 1em 1.2em;
				border-radius: 4px;
				margin: 1.5em 0;
			}
			.summary p:first-child {
				margin-top: 0;
			}
			.summary p:last-child {
				margin-bottom: 0;
			}
		</style>
	</head>

	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="prose">
				<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
				<p><em>Last updated: May 7, 2026</em></p>

				<div class="summary">
					<p><strong>Short version:</strong> paulxie.com is a static site with no backend and no user accounts. The interactive demos run entirely in your browser. If you sign in with Google in a demo, we ask only for permission to call the Gemini API on your behalf — not your name, email, or profile. The token stays in your browser; we never see it, your prompts, or your results.</p>
				</div>

				<h2>What we collect</h2>
				<p>Nothing on the site itself. No accounts, no analytics, no tracking.</p>
				<p>The demos (currently <em>Code RAG Chatbot</em> and <em>Invoice Parse</em>) optionally use Google Sign-In so they can call Google's Gemini API using your own quota. They request only these scopes:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><code>generative-language.peruserquota</code> — call the Gemini API on your behalf</li>
					<li><code>generative-language.retriever</code> — use the Gemini API retriever feature</li>
				</ul>
				<p>No name, email, profile picture, contacts, or files.</p>

				<h2>How the token is handled</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Stored in your browser's <code>localStorage</code> for the session.</li>
					<li>Sent directly from your browser to Google. Never sent to us.</li>
					<li>Expires automatically (about an hour) and can be revoked at any time.</li>
				</ul>
				<p>If you paste a Gemini API key instead, the same applies — it stays in your browser.</p>

				<h2>Third parties</h2>
				<p>The demos talk directly to Google for sign-in and inference. That interaction is governed by <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a> and the <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gemini API Additional Terms</a>. The site is served as static files by a hosting provider, which may process standard request metadata to deliver the site.</p>

				<h2>Your rights</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Revoke the demo's Google access anytime at <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">myaccount.google.com/permissions</a>.</li>
					<li>Clear browser storage for paulxie.com to remove any stored token or API key.</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Changes &amp; contact</h2>
				<p>Updates will be posted here with a new revision date. Questions: <a href="mailto:paulxiep@outlook.com">paulxiep@outlook.com</a>.</p>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
